<p><b>What is girl boss feminism?</b> I wanted to be a “#girlboss.” The term is defined as “the melding of professional self, identity, and capitalist aspiration.” I wanted to become a billionaire CEO of a company, not because I knew what such a job would entail, but because that was what I was told I should become; the money didn't hurt.</p>
<p><b>Who is the real Annie in girlboss?</b> Sadly, the friends Amoruso surrounded herself with – the neighbour played by RuPaul, and her very likeable best friend, Annie, never actually existed in real life. Creator Kay Cannon added these lovable characters to Amoruso's story to make it more cinematic.</p>
