<p><b>Why is the girl boss not just the boss?</b> This language inadvertently negates the importance of their position by placing an exclusive focus on their gender. Simply put, calling a female leader a "girl boss" or a "mompreneur" can suggest that her gender or traditional gender role is more important than her professional qualifications and experience.</p>
<p><b>What is the new term for girlboss?</b> The term “girlboss” celebrates women who dominate in their respective fields, symbolizing empowerment and breaking glass ceilings. However, given the lack of work-life balance being a girlboss entails, a new term has started to gain traction—the “snail girl era.”</p>
